# Environment Configuration Example

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your Supabase credentials.

## Supabase Connection (Remote Database)
```
DB_HOST=db.xxxxx.supabase.co
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=your_password_here
DB_NAME=postgres
```

## Service Configuration
```
SERVICE_PORT=5004
SERVICE_HOST=0.0.0.0
```

## Microservice URLs
```
TEXT_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:5001
SPEECH_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:5002
RETRIEVE_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:5003
DATABASE_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:5004
REALTIME_VOICE_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:5005
REALTIME_VOICE_SERVICE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:5005/ws/realtime-voice
```

## Realtime Voice OpenAI Configuration
```
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
OPENAI_REALTIME_MODEL=gpt-realtime
OPENAI_REALTIME_TRANSCRIPTION_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini-transcribe
OPENAI_REALTIME_VOICE=alloy
OPENAI_REALTIME_USE_EPHEMERAL_TOKEN=true
```

## Notes
- Get DB_HOST and DB_PASSWORD from Supabase Project Settings → Database
- DB_PORT is usually 5432
- DB_USER is usually "postgres"
- DB_NAME is usually "postgres" (Supabase default)
- Never commit this file to git (add to .gitignore)
